Author: allbits#5898
Content: State of the ETH report: I've been messing around today with ETH dapps to see what's out there these days, since there is so much ongoing dapp development and people are making neat stuff. Bottom line is that transaction fees remain absurd.  To send funds between my own wallets, a common occurrence when you're playing around, cost me eleven cents. Making a trade on kyber cost me two dollars!! To use uniswap so I could onboard at synthetix cost me eighty seven cents! Seems their model is busted!. UXs are great tho! All on mobile using Trust Wallet.

Content:
I just created a new website, Privacy Alternatives - it's a directory for privacy tools.
Part of it is dedicated to crypto and I also included many projects from Komodo (ARRR, Barterlly, Zaddex, AtomicDex, Veruscoin and also Pungo, Ocean, AgamaVerus, Chameleon wallets)

https://privacyalternatives.com/
